re): variant of   Barrett  ."]},{"name":"Baratta","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Carmine, Pasquale, Alfonse, Antonio, Carmela, Guido, Salvatore, Vincenzo.","Italian: occupational name for a market trader, especially in northern Italy, from <i>baratta</i> ‘exchange, sale, buying and selling’, a derivative of <i>barattare</i> ‘to barter’. See also   Barrett  ."]},{"name":"Barritt","meanings":["English: variant of   Barrett  ."]},{"name":"Barratt","meanings":["English: variant of   Barrett  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Barrett was born on 21 September 1380, in Minsterworth, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas Barrett Of Bellhouse In Aveley, was 27 and his mother, Elizabeth Norton, was 25. He married Alice Belhouse about 1401, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died on 31 October 1440, in his hometown, at the age of 60."},"et":{"21 Sep 1380–31 Oct 1440":"21. september 1380–31. oktoober 1440","1380–1440":"1380–1440","1380–1405":"1380–1405","1398–1418":"1398–1418","1405–1440":"1405–1440","1418–1475":"1418–1475","1353–1400":"1353–1400","1355–1380":"1355–1380","about 1 April 1440":"umbes 1. aprill 1440","about 5 October 1405":"umbes 5. oktoober 1405","1440":"1440","21 Sep 1380":"21. september 1380","Abt 1401":"umbes 1401","1380":"1380","1400":"1400","about 1405":"umbes 1405","1355":"1355","1475":"1475","1398":"1398","1353":"1353","1418":"1418","31 Oct 1440":"31. oktoober 1440","1405":"1405","Minsterworth, Gloucestershire, England":"Minsterworth, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Mitley